AD_Column.Help: An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.

AD_Column.Name: Guarantee Days
AD_Column.Description: Number of days the product is guaranteed or available
AD_Column.Help: If the value is 0, there is no limit to the availability or guarantee, otherwise the guarantee date is calculated by adding the days to the delivery date.

AD_Column.Name: Min Guarantee Days
AD_Column.Help: When selecting batch/products with a guarantee date, the minimum left guarantee days for automatic picking. You can pick any batch/product manually.

AD_Column.Name: Comment/Help
AD_Column.Help: The Help field contains a hint, comment or help about the use of this item.

AD_Column.Name: Image URL
AD_Column.Help: URL of image; The image is not stored in the database, but retrieved at runtime. The image can be a gif, jpeg or png.

AD_Column.Name: Active
AD_Column.Description: The record is active in the system
AD_Column.Help: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reports. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for audit purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are invoices for this partner record existing. You de-activate the Business Partner and prevent that this record is used for future entries.

AD_Column.Name: Bill of Materials
AD_Column.Help: The Bill of Materials check box indicates if this product consists of a bill of materials.

AD_Column.Name: Drop Shipment
AD_Column.Description: Drop Shipments are sent from the Vendor directly to the Customer
AD_Column.Help: Drop Shipments do not cause any Inventory reservations or movements as the Shipment is from the Vendor's inventory. The Shipment of the Vendor to the Customer must be confirmed.

AD_Column.Name: Exclude Auto Delivery
AD_Column.Help: The product is excluded from generating Shipments. This allows manual creation of shipments for high demand items. If selected, you need to create the shipment manually. But, the item is always included, when the delivery rule of the Order is Force (e.g. for POS). This allows finer granularity of the Delivery Rule Manual.

AD_Column.Name: Print detail records on invoice
AD_Column.Description: Print detail BOM elements on the invoice
AD_Column.Help: The Print Details on Invoice indicates that the BOM element products will print on the Invoice as opposed to this product.

AD_Column.Name: Phantom
AD_Column.Help: Phantom Component are not stored and produced with the product. This is an option to avild maintaining an Engineering and Manufacturing Bill of Materials.

AD_Column.Name: Print detail records on pick list
AD_Column.Description: Print detail BOM elements on the pick list
AD_Column.Help: The Print Details on Pick List indicates that the BOM element products will print on the Pick List as opposed to this product.

AD_Column.Name: Purchased
AD_Column.Help: The Purchased check box indicates if this product is purchased by this organization.

AD_Column.Name: Self-Service
AD_Column.Description: This is a Self-Service entry or this entry can be changed via Self-Service
AD_Column.Help: Self-Service allows users to enter data or update their data. The flag indicates, that this record was entered or created via Self-Service or that the user can change it via the Self-Service functionality.

AD_Column.Name: Mail Template
AD_Column.Help:
The Mail Template indicates the mail template for return messages. Mail text can include variables. The priority of parsing is User/Contact, Business Partner and then the underlying business object (like Request, Dunning, Workflow object).
So, @Name@ would resolve into the User name (if user is defined defined), then Business Partner name (if business partner is defined) and then the Name of the business object if it has a Name.

There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for audit purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are invoices for this partner record existing. You de-activate the Business Partner and prevent that this record is used for future entries.

AD_Field_Trl.Help: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reports.
